begin_memory_text: We talked about a variety of things including where we lived, what we did as hobbies, our common Christianity, and primarily we discussed disability and disability advocacy. We also discussed how people with disabilities should be seen as regular individuals, just like everyone else.
middle_memory_text: Well, I kind of discussed our conversation in the previous question. However, in the middle of the conversation we were talking about how people used to be treated in mental health institutions and in society back in the day, especially the early 60s, because she had brothers and sisters with disabilities in the 60s, and I have a disability myself.
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation, we talked about how we could stay in touch after the conversation was over. I believe I made a lifelong friend even though she was much older than me because she represents and supports something that is so very important to my life.
rest_of_day_open: Well the weekend is upon us. I tend to be very relaxed on the weekend, doing a bunch of enjoyable activities such as watching movies, playing computer games, and watching television. So I don't expect the rest of the week to be too strenuous. I'm also looking forward to it because my mom and her fianc√© are going to come over and see me this weekend.
critical_positive:
I think one thing that worked out well is that my conversation partner, Robin, was a female. I have a lot of anxiety when talking to males because of experiences I have had in the past.

Another thing that went well was that we had a lot in common. This made the conversation flow very easily and quickly.
critical_negative: The only thing that I can think of that did not go well during the conversation was the time limit that we had for the conversation itself. I would have enjoyed continuing the conversation for a lot longer and getting to know Robin a lot more. In fact, we have made plans to stay in touch outside of the conversation itself.
